Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Status conference on November 7, 2022 at 10:30 am.

[MK] cases #22CF224 and #22CF475 called at 3:43pm
Defendant Miguel A Guadalajara Jr. appears in court, in custody, with Attorney Karl Huebner.  ADA Michael Witt in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Mr. Guadalajara indicates that his address is:  711 LaBelle Street, Watertown 53098.

Initial Appearance is held in Case # 22CF475: 
--Service of Complaint admitted, reading waived, the charges and maximum penalties are recited.
--Preliminary Hearing time limit is waived by both parties.
--The Court requires a $100 Cash Bond with condition:
--no presence at the Watertown Senior Center or within 1000' of the Watertown Senior Center 
--The Court appoints Attorney Huebner as counsel.

Prelim-Waiver and Arraignment is held in Case #22CF224: 
--Mr. Guadalajara waives his right to Preliminary Hearing; the Court accepts this waiver and binds him over for Trial.
--Service of Information admitted, reading waived; the charges and maximum penalties are recited
--pleas of "not guilty" are entered
--in response to the Court's inquiry, both counsel indicate that they are not requesting speedy trial.
recess 3:58pm
